This paper is about model-based reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper focuses on analyzing the performance of RL algorithms in the finite-state finite-horizon MDP setting, which is a common setting in RL research. The paper also introduces a novel analysis of real-time dynamic programming, which is a technique commonly used in RL. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Additionally, since the paper deals with control and optimization problems, it could also belong to cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems).
